quran[18]{c,v,t}:
  26,105,The people of Noah cried lies to the Envoys
  26,106,"when their brother Noah said to them, 'Will you not be godfearing"
  26,107,I am for you a faithful Messenger
  26,108,"so serve you God, and obey you me"
  26,109,I ask of you no wage for this; my wage falls only upon the Lord of all Being
  26,110,"so fear you God, and obey you me"
  26,111,"They said, 'Shall we believe thee, whom the vilest follow"
  26,112,"He said, 'What knowledge have I of that they have been doing"
  26,113,"Their account falls only upon my Lord, were you but aware"
  26,114,I would not drive away the believers
  26,115,I am naught but a plain warner
  26,116,"They said, 'If thou givest not over, Noah, thou shalt assuredly be one of the stoned"
  26,117,"He said, 'My Lord, my people have cried me lies"
  26,118,"so give true deliverance between me and them, and deliver me and the believers that are with me"
  26,119,"So We delivered him, and those with him, in the laden ship"
  26,120,then afterwards We drowned the rest
  26,121,"Surely in that is a sign, yet most of them are not believers"
  26,122,"Surely thy Lord, He is the All-mighty, the All-compassionate"